Hi! Welcome to The BarberShop with Shantanu (TBWS). 

TBWS is a series of conversations with founders/CEOs where we explore entrepreneurship and everything that goes with it. At least, we try to. :) 

Stay tuned for a new episode every Friday 6 pm starting August 5th. Hope you enjoy! :)

2 Gen Zs vs 2 Founders.

This time, we’re talking about Is Organisational Loyalty Overrated?

Shantanu is joined by Arshi Gupta [Senior Associate, Investments at Singularity AMC] and
Ishan Gulati [Chief of Staff to CEO at Rebel Foods], voices from Gen Z who bring a fresh perspective on what loyalty looks like in today’s workplace.

Across the table are Luis Miranda [Former Bank Treasurer at HDFC & Ex-CEO at IDFC] and Aseem Dhru [MD & CEO at SBFC Finance Limited], leaders who’ve built successful organisations without compromising their own vision of loyalty.

They’re answering the big questions:
Is loyalty a dying value in today’s workforce?
Or has the definition shifted with Gen Z’s expectations?

Episode drops today at 8 p.m. sharp!

This episode of The Bridge brings together 2 Gen Zs and 2 CEOs to expose what really makes personal brands work today - from authenticity to strategy. Also what CEOs think about their employees building personal brand.

Watch the full episode to get all the tea that has been spilled.

2 Gen Zs vs 2 Founders.

This time, we’re talking about personal branding.
Shantanu is joined by Avani Rathore (Entrepreneur and Ex-BCG) and Goutami Rane (Senior Account Executive at Ogilvy), voices who’ve grown their presence online.

Across the table are Revant Bhate (Co-Founder & CEO, Mosaic Wellness) and Kaushik Mukherjee (Co-Founder & COO, SUGAR Cosmetics), leaders who built brands without becoming one.

They’re answering the big questions:
Is visibility the new currency at work?
Or just another form of pressure?

Episode 2 drops tomorrow at 8 p.m. sharp!
